<item>
            <title>[WICKET-4589] Closing &lt;/wicket:container&gt; tag is incorrectly setup as autocomponent</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4589</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The closing instance of the &amp;lt;wicket:container&amp;gt; tag returns true when isAutoComponentTag() is called whereas the opening instance correctly returns false.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem lies probably in the WicketTagIdentifier class which simply checks if there is a wicket:id attribute value and makes all tags (opening or closing) autocomponent tags if there is no wicket:id.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Obviously any closing tag doesnt have a wicket:id assigned.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
